data.prompt:
Dìu em đến đem cho đời anh thôi hoang vắng
Tim ta say đắm đã yêu em trọn cuộc tình
Dòng tháng năm đó đã cho tình yêu em tha thiết
Những ái ân để phôi pha
Đành với duyên kiếp, em bước đi trong chiều mưa rơi
Lặng đứng trên bến, anh với trông thuyền ra khơi
Những tháng năm đếm lá theo mùa thu chết, những thu chết
Xuân về cho cây xanh lá
Cớ riêng mình anh lạc mất mùa xuân
Đêm đêm nằm nghe hồn bâng khuâng
Bên song anh trông đầu non trăng xế
Thương bèo trôi theo sông nước
Biết bây giờ em lạc bước về đâu
Tương tư về thương đôi mắt nâu
Đêm đêm tìm trong màn tối muôn sao

Ngồi suốt canh vắng lãng quên sầu thương trong men đắng
Cơn say mê đắm sóng dâng cao ngọn thủy triều
Rồi thấy thấp thoáng bóng em về chìm trong đáy cốc
Đôi mắt ưu buồn thiên thu
Rồi nắng mai đến mây trắng bay khi tàn cơn say
Tình đã xa vắng nỗi nhớ vẫn còn đâu đây
Những tháng năm đến lá theo mùa thu chết, những thu chết
Xuân về cho cây xanh lá
Cớ sao tình ta chỉ có mùa thu
Đêm đêm nằm nghe hồn tương tư
Bên song đầu non tàn canh bóng xế
Thương bèo trôi theo muôn hướng
Biết bây giờ em lạc bước về đâu
Em ơi, chờ em đến kiếp nào
Xin cho ngày sau mình mãi bên nhau

Xuân về cho cây xanh lá
Cớ sao tình ta chỉ có mùa thu
Đêm đêm nằm nghe hồn tương tư
Bên song đầu non tàn canh bóng xế
Thương bèo trôi theo muôn hướng
Biết bây giờ em lạc bước về đâu

data.text:
[Verse 1]
Breath in the dark air
Keys in a cold hand
Boot prints on concrete
Fading as I stand

Coats on the doorway
Kettle just starts to sing
Your note on the counter
Folded like a wing

[Chorus]
Winter came early
Stayed too long
Got in the walls
Got in our songs
You said
"Love is work
" then you moved on
I’m still here
Humming our winter song

[Verse 2]
Mug with your lipstick
Corner chipped from the fall
Phone full of photos
I don't open at all

Street on a Sunday
Quiet as fresh snow
Every small silence
Sounds like your hello

[Chorus]
Winter came early
Stayed too long
Got in the walls
Got in our songs
You said
"Love is work
" then you moved on
I’m still here
Humming our winter song

[Bridge]
Maybe by April
This chill will break
Maybe the thaw comes
With one small mistake

[Chorus]
Winter came early
Stayed too long
Got in the walls
Got in our songs
You said
"Love is work
" then you moved on
I’m still here
Humming our winter song
Just right here
Humming our winter song
data.title: Snow On The Backsteps

data.text:
[Verse 1]
Breath on the glass
Names in the fog
Kettle complaining
Old ticking clock
Wool on my wrists
Hands still cold
Same chipped mug
Same stories we told

[Chorus]
Stay till the winter’s gone
Stay till the light grows long
We’ll count the nights
By the quiet of the house
Stay till the thaw begins
Stay through the howling wind
I’ll put another log on
You don’t have to go out

[Verse 2]
Boots by the door
Melted ring of brown
Radio humming
Small hometown sound
Snow on the cars
Street turned gray
Your head on my shoulder
World far away

[Chorus]
Stay till the winter’s gone
Stay till the light grows long
We’ll count the nights
By the quiet of the house
Stay till the thaw begins
Stay through the howling wind
I’ll put another log on
You don’t have to go out

[Bridge]
Every season
Says it won’t last
We’re just learning
How to bend with it
If the roads close
Let the roads close
We’ve got blankets
We’ve got time to sit (yeah)

[Chorus]
Stay till the winter’s gone
Stay till the light grows long
We’ll count the nights
By the quiet of the house
Stay till the thaw begins
Stay through the howling wind
I’ll put another log on
You don’t have to go out

[Verse 1]
You tap your pen
On a coffee-stained page
Say
“This is only practice
I don’t feel a thing today”

[Chorus]
But my test pattern heart
Glows in black and white for you
Little lines
Little sparks
Every trial pulls me through
Call it random
Call it art
I just call it wanting you
My test pattern heart
Learning how to beat for two

[Verse 2]
You shrug and laugh
“At least the rhyme is clean”
Like we’re only doing drills
Not rewiring what we mean

[Chorus]
‘Cause my test pattern heart
Glows in black and white for you
Little lines
Little sparks
Every trial pulls me through
Call it random
Call it art
I just call it wanting you
My test pattern heart
Learning how to beat for two

data.prompt:
[Verse 1]
Woke up to gold on my window
Dust in the air doing slow turns
Coffee cup hot in my left hand
Your name on my screen and my heart burns

[Chorus]
Sunshine on repeat
Running through my chest like a heartbeat
Every little ray has your heartbeat
Lighting up the corners of my mind
Sunshine on repeat
Spilling on the floor where our feet meet
Turning every Monday to sweet heat
Leave the cloudy days behind

[Verse 2]
Laugh lines deep in our selfies
Sidewalk chalk on your blue jeans
Traffic hums soft in the background
You spin me around like a daydream (hey!)

[Chorus]
Sunshine on repeat
Running through my chest like a heartbeat
Every little ray has your heartbeat
Lighting up the corners of my mind
Sunshine on repeat
Spilling on the floor where our feet meet
Turning every Monday to sweet heat
Leave the cloudy days behind

[Bridge]
If the rain comes in
Let it
We got bright stored up inside
Pull the curtains back
Set it free
Watch the shadows run and hide (oh)

[Chorus]
Sunshine on repeat
Running through my chest like a heartbeat
Every little ray has your heartbeat
Lighting up the corners of my mind
Sunshine on repeat
Spilling on the floor where our feet meet
Turning every Monday to sweet heat
Leave the cloudy days behind
data.tags: pop, Bright pop with glossy acoustic guitar and snappy drums, light synth plucks filling the edges. Female vocals, crisp and playful. Verses stay tight and bouncy; chorus explodes with stacked harmonies and claps. Middle lift adds a brief dreamy pad swell before dropping back into a final, hook-heavy chorus.
data.title: Sunshine On Repeat
